pments old and new. By looking closely at the composition of science epics and the related genres developed along with them, we are able to view the historical narrative of science as a form of knowledge itself, one that discloses much about the development of our understanding of and relationship to science over time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aSciencexHistoriography. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 4acosmic evolution. 4adogma of unity. 4afinal story. 4afinal theory. 4agenre of synthesis. 4anatural history. 4ascientific epic. 4ascientific myth. 4auniversal history. 70(DE-601)1062193240(DE-588)4041421-8aNaturwissenschaften2gnd 70(DE-601)1063380990(DE-588)4015025-2aEpik2gnd 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226500737423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226500737.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles